message.content: Since $\alpha$ is inversely proportional to $\beta$, we have $\alpha\beta = k$ for some constant $k$.  When $\alpha = 4$ and $\beta = 9$, we get $k = \alpha\beta = 4(9) = 36$.  When $\beta = -72$, $\alpha \beta = (-72) \alpha = -72 \alpha$, so $-72 \alpha = 36$, which means $\alpha = \boxed{-\frac{1}{2}}$.
